# Roblox-TS Rules

This codebase uses [roblox-ts](mdc:https:/roblox-ts.com), a TypeScript-to-Luau compiler for Roblox development.

## General Guidelines

- All Roblox game code should be written in TypeScript following the roblox-ts patterns
- Use the official Roblox services via the `@rbxts/services` package
- Follow TypeScript best practices for type safety

## Imports

- Use the roblox-ts standard import format: `import { Service } from "@rbxts/services";`
- For project files, use relative imports: `import { MyClass } from "./MyClass";`

- Dont import Vector3 from `import { Vector3 } from "@rbxts/rbx-types";`. It is global

## Type Safety

- Leverage TypeScript's static type system for all code
- Avoid using `any` type when possible
- Use interfaces and type aliases to create reusable type definitions

## Roblox-specific Patterns

- Use roblox-ts event connection syntax:
    ```typescript
    part.Touched.Connect((otherPart) => {
    	// Handle touch event
    });
    ```
- When working with Roblox instances, check types with `.IsA()` before operations

- use array .size() instead of.length



